addOwner(address).details: Allows to add a new owner. Transaction has to be sent by wallet.

allowance(address,address).details: Function to check the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

params.owner: address The address which owns the funds.
params.spender: address The address which will spend the funds.

allowance(address,address).return: A uint256 specifying the amount of tokens still available for the spender.

approve(address,uint256).details: Approve the passed address to spend the specified amount of tokens on behalf of msg.sender. Beware that changing an allowance with this method brings the risk that someone may use both the old and the new allowance by unfortunate transaction ordering. One possible solution to mitigate this race condition is to first reduce the spender's allowance to 0 and set the desired value afterwards: https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/20#issuecomment-263524729

params.spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params.value: The amount of tokens to be spent.

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address.

params.owner: The address to query the balance of.

balanceOf(address).return: An uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address.

burn(uint256,bytes).details: Allows an user to burn the token.

changeRequirement(uint256).details: Allows to change the number of required confirmations. Transaction has to be sent by wallet.

confirmTransaction(uint256).details: Allows an owner to confirm a transaction.

decimals().return: the number of decimals of the token.

executeTransaction(uint256).details: Allows anyone to execute a confirmed transaction.

getConfirmationCount(uint256).details: Returns number of confirmations of a transaction.

getConfirmations(uint256).details: Returns array with owner addresses, which confirmed transaction.

getTransactionCount(bool,bool).details: Returns total number of transactions after filers are applied.
getTransactionCount(bool,bool).return: Total number of transactions after filters are applied.

getTransactionIds(uint256,uint256,bool,b.details: Returns list of transaction IDs in defined range.

params.from: Index start position of transaction array.
params.to: Index end position of transaction array.

isConfirmed(uint256).details: Returns the confirmation status of a transaction.

minFee().details: The amount fee that will be lost when transferring.

removeOwner(address).details: Allows to remove an owner. Transaction has to be sent by wallet.

replaceOwner(address,address).details: Allows to replace an owner with a new owner. Transaction has to be sent by wallet.

params.owner: Address of owner to be replaced.

revokeConfirmation(uint256).details: Allows an owner to revoke a confirmation for a transaction.

submitTransaction(address,uint256,bytes).details: Allows an owner to submit and confirm a transaction.

totalSupply().details: Total number of tokens in existence

transfer(address,uint256).details: Transfer token for a specified address

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfer tokens from one address to another

params.from: address The address which you want to send tokens from
params.to: address The address which you want to transfer to
params.value: uint256 the amount of tokens to be transferred
